<html>
<head>
	<title>receiptomatic login</title>
	<link href = "/static/css/main.css" rel = "stylesheet" type = "text/css" />
</head>
<body>
	<center>
<tmpl_if name = "logged_in" value = "no">
	<big><span class = "input_error">Login Failure. Please try again</span></big><p />
<tmpl_elsif name = "enabled" value = "no">
	<big><span class = "input_error">Account has been disabled</span></big><p />
</tmpl_if>
	<big><i>Welcome to</i> <big>receiptomatic</big></big><p />
	<form action = "/login/" method = "POST">
	<table>
	<tbody>
	<tr>
		<td><big>Username </big></td>
		<td> : <input type = "text" name = "username" size = "32" maxlength = "255"></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td><big>Password </big></td>
		<td> : <input type = "password" name = "password" size = "32" maxlength = "255"></td>
	</tr>
	</table>
	</tbody>
	<small>Restrict this session to your IP address: <input type = "checkbox" name = "restrict_ip" value = "true" checked /></small>
	<p />
	<input type = "submit" value = "Open Sesame" />
	</form>
	<p />
	<br />
	<span class = "lighter"><small>Click <a href = "/forgotten_password/">here</a> if you have forgotten your password.</small></span>
	</center>

	<p />

	<div id = "cookie_note">
	<br /><br />
	<small>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>NOTE: </strong>This site requires functioning cookies. When you log in, one cookie, "session_id" is created in your<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;browser. This is used for security to identify you to the application during your session.
	<p />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The cookie is set to last only for the current browser session (session cookie) and if you use the<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"logout" link, it will be removed immediately.
	</small>
	</div>

	<footer>
	<small>Â© OpenTech Labs, 2011-2012. This software is licensed under the GNU Affero General Public License v3</small>
	</footer>
</body>
</html>
